                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="engraving" xml:id="d1">Four images engraved on paper of the apostles and the Saviour and eight images engraved on paper of other apostles and Our Lady Mary are glued at the beginning and at the end of the book, respectively. 
                  They are of the <date>16th century</date>.
               </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="engraving" xml:id="d2">
                  Engravings of Our Lady of Sorrows and of the Holy Trinity engraved by <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11204Graffico">Camillo Graffico</persName> and crudely drawn, before <locus target="#3">f. 1</locus>.
               </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>The shelfmark <q xml:lang="la">Vat. | 3 | Aethiop.</q> is written on the cover, together with the coat of arms of pope <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7893PiusIX">Pius IX</persName>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
